       #include <dshm.h>

       size_t    dshm_alignment (void);

DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       dshm_alignment  returns  the  minimum  legal alignment, in
       bytes, for a DSHM map.  The starting logical  address  and
       size  of  the  map  must  both be multiples of this value,
       which must be a power of 2.

RReettuurrnn vvaalluueess
       If dshm_alignment returns 0, DSHM is not supported.

       Otherwise, dshm_alignment returns the minimum  map  align-
       ment, in bytes.

   EErrrroorrss
       No errors are currently defined.

